1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes a new video classification methodology that involves capturing appearance and motion information from videos, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed methodology involves using pre-trained networks and a novel pooling operator for feature extraction, which are common techniques in machine learning. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video classification, which is a subfield of multimedia. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed methodology involves using machine learning techniques for video classification, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves extracting features from videos, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval.
